get.description: Fetch a paginated list of treatment schemas, filtered by the user's current selected hospital. The results include detailed information about each treatment schema, such as periodicity, product information, and other optional nested relationship data, depending on query parameters.

parameters.description: The page number of the paginated results to retrieve.
parameters.name: page

parameters.description: The number of items to retrieve per page in the paginated results.
parameters.name: rowsPerPage

parameters.description: Descending sorting order. If true, the order is descending, if it is false or non-present, the order is ascending.
parameters.name: descending

parameters.description: Filter results by name, allowing substring matching.
parameters.name: filter[name]

parameters.description: Filter results by status (e.g., active/inactive). Typically, `1` for active and `0` for inactive records.
parameters.name: filter[status]

200.description: A paginated list of treatment schemas.

per_page.description: Number of items included per page.

total_pages.description: Total number of pages available based on the given number per page.

category.description: Details of the category (e.g., Oncology, Radiology) of the schema.

created_at.description: Timestamp of when the schema was created.

description.description: Detailed description of the treatment schema.

edited_at.description: Timestamp of the most recent update to the schema.

hospital_id.description: ID of the hospital associated with the schema.

notes.example: Requires close monitoring for potential adverse reactions.

periodicity.description: Details of the periodicity of the schema (if available).

post_medication.example: Drink fluids and take prescribed painkillers.

preparation_instructions.description: Instructions for preparation before administering the schema.

schema_products.description: List of products associated with the schema (optional, depending on nested depth queried).

product_id.description: Product ID linked to the schema.

series_count.description: The number of cycle series in the schema.

status.description: Status of the schema (e.g., 1 for active, 0 for inactive).

uuid.description: Unique identifier for the treatment schema.

401.description: Unauthorized - The user is not authenticated or the access token is expired.

403.description: Forbidden - User lacks the required permissions to access this endpoint.

500.description: Internal server error due to an unexpected exception during back-end processing.

error.example: Unhandled database exception during query execution.

post.description: This endpoint creates a new treatment schema for the hospital associated with the authenticated user. The schema details include products and periodicity.

parameters.description: JSON payload for the treatment schema.
parameters.name: body

example.name: This field is required.
example.schema_products: This field must be an array.

401.description: Authorization error (e.g., hospital mismatch).

delete.description: This endpoint deletes a specific treatment schema by its `uuid`. The `schema_products` associated with the treatment schema will also be removed from the database. Requires valid hospital context and proper user permissions.

parameters.description: Unique identifier (`uuid`) of the treatment schema to delete. Must be a valid UUID format.
parameters.name: uuid

details.description: Additional information about the deleted treatment schema.

400.description: The request was invalid. Possible causes include: - Invalid `uuid` format. - Treatment schema not found.

error.example: The provided UUID does not correspond to an existing treatment schema.

403.description: Forbidden. Possible reasons include: - The user does not have sufficient permissions to delete treatment schemas. - The treatment schema belongs to a hospital the user does not have access to.

error.example: You do not have permission to delete treatment schemas for this hospital.

500.description: Internal server error occurred during the deletion process. This is typically caused by unexpected database errors or other unhandled exceptions.

error.example: Unexpected database error occurred while deleting the treatment schema.

get.description: Retrieves the details of a specific treatment schema based on its unique identifier (`uuid`) and the user's authenticated hospital context. This endpoint requires an access token for authentication, and the treatment schema must belong to the hospital associated with the user making the request. The response includes details about the treatment schema and can include related objects such as `schema_products`, `periodicity`, and `category` if the optional `jsondepth` query parameter is specified.

parameters.description: Unique identifier (`uuid`) of the treatment schema to retrieve. This must be a valid UUID format and correspond to an existing treatment schema in the database.
parameters.name: uuid

parameters.description: Numeric value indicating the depth of nested objects to include in the response. A higher value retrieves more detailed relationships.
parameters.name: jsondepth

category.description: Optional relationship data for the category parameter (shown when `jsondepth > 0`).

periodicity.description: Optional relationship data for the periodicity parameter (shown when `jsondepth > 0`).

post_medication.example: Drink plenty of fluids and take prescribed painkillers post-administration.

pre_medication.example: Take antihistamine one hour before chemotherapy.

preparation_instructions.example: Dilute drug with saline before infusion.

schema_products.description: Optional list of associated schema products (shown when `jsondepth > 0`).

400.description: Invalid request due to malformed input or the treatment schema `uuid` not being found for the user's hospital.

error.example: The specified treatment schema does not exist.

403.description: Forbidden. This happens when the user is authenticated, but the request treatment schema does not belong to the user's hospital context.

error.example: Treatment schema is not accessible for the current user's hospital context.

500.description: Internal server error due to unexpected errors in the back-end processing.

error.example: Unhandled exception occurred during database query.

put.description: Updates an existing treatment schema for a hospital. The hospital is determined from the JWT token of the authenticated user. The `code` must be unique within the hospital's treatment schemas.
